 which have never before been translated into English. It opens with a broad-ranging explanation of the historical background to the translated texts and then each source is accompanied by a full commentary and an introductory essay exploring its authorship, language and subject matter. The sources are rich in the detail of Merovingian political life. Their subjects are the powerful in society and they reveal the successful interplay between power and sanctity, a process which came to underpin much of European culture throughout the early Middle Ages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian hagiography. 0aChurch historyyMiddle Ages, 600-1500xHistoriography. 0aMerovingianszFrancexHistory. 4aMedieval Sources 2013. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aActa Aunemundi.  aAdditamentum Nivialense de Fuilano.  aLiber Historiae Francorum.  aMerovingian Frankish kingdom.  aMerovingian hagiography.  aPassio Leudegarii.  aPassio Praejecti.  aVita Audoini Episcopi Rotomagensis.  aVita Domnae Balthidis.  aVita Sanctae Geretrudis.  apeace-making element.  apolitical narrative.1 aFouracre, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerberding, Richard A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGerberding, Richard A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611278140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526112781423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526112781/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles